The paper deals with deep convolutional networks and their ability to learn transferable features for multiple tasks. This is a common problem in machine learning, and the paper proposes a novel approach to address it. Given that the paper deals with deep learning, computer vision, and natural language processing, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
